<div id="review_3339666949" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3339666949" />
    <a title="Barbara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32662770-barbara"><img alt="Barbara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1538734547p2/32662770.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3339666949?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barbara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barbara" href="/user/show/32662770-barbara">Barbara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/22034850-dear-leader">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32662770-barbara?shelf=korea">korea</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32662770-barbara?shelf=autobiography">autobiography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3339666949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3527479884708700997">I&apos;ve read a lot of books about North Korea and the people who flee the country&apos;s oppressive regime and &apos;Dear Leader&apos; tells a very similar experience once the author has crossed the frozen river. The big difference between this &apos;I ran away from the Kims&apos; book and most others, is that Jang Jin-Sung had a very privileged insider experience of life close to the ruling family.<br/><br/>Originally a talented musician, he came to the attention of Kim Jung-il through his poetry and at an early age became one of t</span>
  <span id="freeText3527479884708700997" style="display:none">I've read a lot of books about North Korea and the people who flee the country's oppressive regime and 'Dear Leader' tells a very similar experience once the author has crossed the frozen river. The big difference between this 'I ran away from the Kims' book and most others, is that Jang Jin-Sung had a very privileged insider experience of life close to the ruling family.<br /><br />Originally a talented musician, he came to the attention of Kim Jung-il through his poetry and at an early age became one of those working in a department responsible for propaganda and story-telling, having access to South Korean and other foreign books, papers and magazines with a view to writing Kim-praising articles as if he were a South Korean who wanted to move to the North.<br /><br />After a seemingly rather minor incident in which a book that shouldn't have left the propaganda office was found to have been taken home, he and a friend decide to flee the country, using their contacts and privileges to get travel passes to the border.<br /><br />His is an unusual point of view for such a book. He isn't one who suffered the starvation and deprivation of life in North Korea. He was part of the elite upon whom praise and gifts were showered. He never scavenged for blades of grass to make thin soup or counted the grains of rice on his plate. But the fear of being punished for taking a book home sent him to China.<br /><br />This book didn't grab my attention the way that others have. Perhaps because his experience once he reaches China is SO similar to that of other books I've read. Blame me, perhaps for knowing too much and reading too many Korean escapee books.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3527479884708700997" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

