<div id="review_1472748875" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1472748875" />
    <a title="Sarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22667446-sarah"><img alt="Sarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604026721p2/22667446.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1472748875?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah" href="/user/show/22667446-sarah">Sarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1472748875" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6001197068655751662"> Only a few books can make me stay awake for more than 24 hours when the next morning I have to wake up early for university, and &quot;Dear Leader&quot; is one of them. I couldn&apos;t put it down no matter what and it even made me cry at five in the morning. <br/> I already had some information about what goes on in North Korea of oppression, but this book gave me a lot of new information that at several times left me with a dropped jaw and anger. Although I am not that much happy where I live and war or bombings</span>
  <span id="freeText6001197068655751662" style="display:none"> Only a few books can make me stay awake for more than 24 hours when the next morning I have to wake up early for university, and "Dear Leader" is one of them. I couldn't put it down no matter what and it even made me cry at five in the morning. <br /> I already had some information about what goes on in North Korea of oppression, but this book gave me a lot of new information that at several times left me with a dropped jaw and anger. Although I am not that much happy where I live and war or bombings happened in the past, I feel so lucky and privileged that I was born here and not in North Korea. The worth thing ever is living a life with no freedom. I hope with all of my heart that one day the people of North Korea will know freedom.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6001197068655751662" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
