    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1522941463" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1522941463" />
    <a title="Sud666" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36890366-sud666"><img alt="Sud666" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1418437112p2/36890366.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1522941463?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sud666" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sud666" href="/user/show/36890366-sud666">Sud666</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/36890366-sud666?shelf=political-science">political-science</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1522941463" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11031996769010189931">This book is a must read for anyone wanting to know the inside story of the dystopian Orwellian nightmare that is North Korea. Written by a former poet-laureate and a member of the Admitted (the elite of the elite who have been allowed in the presence of the Dear Leader for more than 20 mins). It tells the story of Jang Jin-sung and his work with the UDF (an organization that writes propoganda as poetry) under Kim Jong-Il. While, not well-written as more polished novelists might write, it is sta</span>
  <span id="freeText11031996769010189931" style="display:none">This book is a must read for anyone wanting to know the inside story of the dystopian Orwellian nightmare that is North Korea. Written by a former poet-laureate and a member of the Admitted (the elite of the elite who have been allowed in the presence of the Dear Leader for more than 20 mins). It tells the story of Jang Jin-sung and his work with the UDF (an organization that writes propoganda as poetry) under Kim Jong-Il. While, not well-written as more polished novelists might write, it is stark and, sometimes, brutally honest. The reader is introduced into the completely mad brain-washed world of North Korea. You will be exposed to the horror of a society that lives in squalid conditions and bombastic non-stop brainwashing that the world though long gone with the demise of Hitler's Germany, Mao's China and Stalin's Russia. Sadly, the NK regime is alive, though to call it "well" would be pushing it. As the regular people starve, literally, the Communist Party lives well-but never too secure as anything and anyone who impinge upon the power of the ruling house of Kim are ruthlessly destroyed. It gives us the history of the first Supreme Leader (Kim Il-sung) and his rise to power and moves to how his son (Kim Jong-il) took over power and instituted the megalomanic cult of personality that is still exploited by the third Kim and current Dear Leader (Kim Jong-un). It shows the awfulness of life there and the constant bombardment of the population by Communist propaganda that turned the populace into brain-washed zombies. It shows the complicity of the Chinese Communists in helping to prop up this disgusting regime and perpetuate this humanitarian catastrophe. The book also tells the story of how Jang was able to escape into China and then evade the Chinese Secret Police who kept trying to apprehend him and return him to NK to face certain execution, with a long bit of torture thrown in first. Luckily, the South Korean Intelligence people were able to smuggle him out. It is a great read for any interested poli-sci student, or anyone just interested in NK.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11031996769010189931" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

