<div id="review_1177670922" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1177670922" />
    <a title="Marko" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10872522-marko"><img alt="Marko" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1342030144p2/10872522.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1177670922?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marko" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marko" href="/user/show/10872522-marko">Marko</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781476766560" href="/book/show/22609347-dear-leader">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10872522-marko?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1177670922" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer128779633284530041">This book was perhaps a slight letdown. It had information about North Korea but probably more than half of the book was dedicated to Jang Jin-Sung and his escape in particular. While it was interesting it was not what I was looking for when I bought this book. <br/><br/>So quite a big part of the roughly 300 pages was not about North Korea. The parts that did were quite interesting, however. Considering the recent confession by Shin Dong-hyuk that he wasn&apos;t completely honest about everything in his book </span>
  <span id="freeText128779633284530041" style="display:none">This book was perhaps a slight letdown. It had information about North Korea but probably more than half of the book was dedicated to Jang Jin-Sung and his escape in particular. While it was interesting it was not what I was looking for when I bought this book. <br /><br />So quite a big part of the roughly 300 pages was not about North Korea. The parts that did were quite interesting, however. Considering the recent confession by Shin Dong-hyuk that he wasn't completely honest about everything in his book <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11797365.Escape_from_Camp_14_One_Man_s_Remarkable_Odyssey_from_North_Korea_to_Freedom_in_the_West" title="Escape from Camp 14 One Man's Remarkable Odyssey from North Korea to Freedom in the West by Blaine Harden" rel="nofollow noopener">Escape from Camp 14: One Man's Remarkable Odyssey from North Korea to Freedom in the West</a> I was left wondering if the same is true about this book. No doubt North Korea is a very, very strange place and the people's suffering there is enormous but there were some things I was still left a bit sceptical about.<br /><br />Overall though, this book still gives an insight into the life and workings of probably the strangest country in the world, the best I have seen so far and helped me understand it much better. Most books and articles are, after all, written by foreigners who haven't lived in the country for real (all foreigners are closely managed so they only see what officials want them to see) so they have to rely on second-hand sources at best. The book also gives insight into the mind of the North Korean leaders, mostly to the mind of now deceased Kim Il-Jong but it does still explain why North Korea do certain things like nuclear tests. Most importantly it explains the command structure better than anything I have seen. Even though I'm uncertain about some events happening like this book describes them I do believe the larger picture is accurate.</span>
  <a data-text-id="128779633284530041" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


